				 Tata Steel recasts board
 OUR BUREAU																								Calcutta, Nov. 22: Tata Steel today recast its board, inducting one more director from Corus, taking its size to 14.																								Andrew Robb was inducted as non-executive independent director and deputy managing director (steel) T. Mukherjee was appointed non-executive director at the board meeting.																								Robb was non-executive director of the Corus group since August 2003.																								The company said Mukherjee retired as deputy managing director (steel) of the company on October 31.																								With Robb, the total number of directors in Tata Steel from Corus is now five.																								The others are James Leng as non-executive deputy chairman and Jacques Schraven and Anthony Hayward as non-executive independent directors.																								Phillippe Varin is part of the board as a non-executive, non-independent director.																								According to the company website, the board consists of chairman R.N. Tata, N.N. Wadia, Subodh Bhargava, S.M. Palia, Suresh Krishna, Ishaat Hussain, J.J. Irani, B. Muthuraman and T. Mukherjee along with five Corus officials.																								Earlier, Tata Steel had said it would come out with a mega rights issue of about Rs 10,000 crore to repay the bridge loans raised to fund the acquisition of Corus. 
